WEBVTT

00:02.203 --> 00:04.737
[ Upbeat Christmas music plays ]

00:12.446 --> 00:15.614
Jessica: You're a good singer,
Mrs. shelmerdine.

00:15.616 --> 00:19.351
In fact... Promotion.

00:19.353 --> 00:22.521
You can take that shaky alto
to the mines, nurse Watkins.

00:24.325 --> 00:26.525
Ooh, Jessica town
is looking great.
[ Squeals ]

00:26.527 --> 00:28.160
[ Chuckles ]

00:28.162 --> 00:30.796
Except I hate seeing
that empty hole every year.

00:30.798 --> 00:33.032
Can't believe instead
of a bakery,

00:33.034 --> 00:34.967
I accidentally bought
two bookshops.

00:34.969 --> 00:36.435
Now they're in competition.

00:39.240 --> 00:42.574
I'll never stop trying
to hunt down

00:42.576 --> 00:44.476
that dickens village
"white horse bakery,"

00:44.478 --> 00:46.545
item number 5926-9.

00:46.547 --> 00:48.313
It's my white whale.

00:48.315 --> 00:49.815
Is that from "Moby dick"?

00:49.817 --> 00:51.083
I feel like that's
one of those books

00:51.085 --> 00:52.317
everybody says they've read,

00:52.319 --> 00:53.585
but nobody's actually read it.

00:53.587 --> 00:55.054
You never read "Moby dick"?

00:55.056 --> 00:56.488
It's an amazing story.

00:56.490 --> 00:59.058
No, I know. I read it.

00:59.060 --> 01:01.760
I see you haven't changed
your views on Santa.

01:01.762 --> 01:03.929
Well, there's room
for improvement.

01:03.931 --> 01:05.731
He flies around the globe
in one night

01:05.733 --> 01:07.332
to give the whole world
presents.

01:07.334 --> 01:08.434
What's there to improve?
[ Sighs ]

01:08.436 --> 01:10.502
He has no higher degree.

01:10.504 --> 01:12.037
If you break it down,

01:12.039 --> 01:14.940
he's either a toy maker
or a glorified deliveryman.

01:14.942 --> 01:17.076
Either way, he's labor,
not management.

01:17.078 --> 01:19.845
Look how long it took him
to promote Rudolph.

01:19.847 --> 01:21.447
Clearly not good
at spotting talent.

01:21.449 --> 01:23.182
And at his weight,

01:23.184 --> 01:25.951
he shouldn't be eating milk and
cookies at every single house.

01:25.953 --> 01:28.087
No, he should just pack himself

01:28.089 --> 01:30.322
a little bag of almonds
and a pear.

01:32.293 --> 01:34.726
Irish mayor.

01:34.728 --> 01:36.762
[ Chuckling ]
Always drinking.

01:36.764 --> 01:37.963
[ Both chuckle ]

01:37.965 --> 01:40.566
Captions by vitac...

01:40.568 --> 01:41.767
¶ fresh off the boat ¶

01:41.769 --> 01:43.402
¶ I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go ¶

01:43.404 --> 01:45.571
¶ if you don't know, homey,
now you know ¶

01:45.573 --> 01:46.905
¶ fresh off the boat ¶

01:46.907 --> 01:49.208
¶ homey, you don't know
where I come from ¶

01:49.210 --> 01:50.876
¶ but I know where I'm goin' ¶

01:50.878 --> 01:53.545
¶ I'm fresh off the boat ¶

01:53.547 --> 01:55.981
[ Christmas music plays ]

02:04.091 --> 02:06.959
[ Speaking Chinese ]

02:13.968 --> 02:16.034
This is my new version
of Eddie's pimp walk.

02:17.238 --> 02:19.438
I call it jazz walk.

02:19.440 --> 02:21.373
No.
This is jazz walk.

02:29.283 --> 02:30.482
[ Chuckles ]

02:30.484 --> 02:31.783
I took intro to Bob fosse

02:31.785 --> 02:33.118
as an elective sophomore year.

02:33.120 --> 02:34.653
You did?
I sure did.

02:34.655 --> 02:36.755
Oh, okay.

02:36.757 --> 02:38.290
Louis, I did it.

02:38.292 --> 02:39.525
I improved Santa.

02:39.527 --> 02:41.793
What do you mean "improved"?

02:41.795 --> 02:44.696
Dad, did you know Santa
was an aeronautical engineer

02:44.698 --> 02:46.465
and an accomplished scientist?

02:46.467 --> 02:47.766
Oh, really?

02:47.768 --> 02:49.134
I thought he was just
a jolly guy

02:49.136 --> 02:50.435
who comes at Christmas.

02:50.437 --> 02:52.871
He is,
but he also went to Princeton.

02:52.873 --> 02:55.007
Mom said he studied every night

02:55.009 --> 02:56.775
and didn't waste time
on girls or beer.

02:56.777 --> 02:59.611
He prefers for people
to focus on his charity work,

02:59.613 --> 03:01.647
but the money
he made from science

03:01.649 --> 03:03.782
is what pays for all the toys.

03:03.784 --> 03:05.217
It makes sense.

03:05.219 --> 03:07.286
He must know physics
to build a flying sleigh.

03:07.288 --> 03:11.056
And if he owns the patent,
he must be m.C. Hammer rich!

03:11.058 --> 03:14.026
Or maybe it's just a part
of the Christmas magic!

03:15.696 --> 03:17.129
What are you doing?

03:17.131 --> 03:18.664
What<i> aren't</i> I doing?

03:18.666 --> 03:20.632
[ Sighs ] You shouldn't
mess with tradition.

03:20.634 --> 03:22.568
Why'd you have to
"improve Santa" all of a sudden?

03:22.570 --> 03:24.369
Because, Louis.

03:24.371 --> 03:27.472
Evan deserves for Santa
to be the best.

03:27.474 --> 03:29.508
We've got the cattleman's ranch
breakfast with Santa

03:29.510 --> 03:31.009
at the restaurant tomorrow.

03:31.011 --> 03:32.244
What happens if Evan asks him

03:32.246 --> 03:33.979
a bunch of math
and science questions?

03:33.981 --> 03:36.148
Just tell whoever's
playing Santa

03:36.150 --> 03:38.717
to brush up on their algebra,
physics, and basic trig.

03:38.719 --> 03:40.452
Mitch is playing Santa.

03:41.589 --> 03:42.754
Can we split the check, please?

03:42.756 --> 03:44.122
Sure.

03:46.860 --> 03:48.894
We need to find a new Santa.

03:48.896 --> 03:50.929
Okay, well,
we need an older white guy

03:50.931 --> 03:52.364
with an advanced degree

03:52.366 --> 03:54.566
who enjoys children sitting
in his lap.

03:58.005 --> 03:59.838
I'd love to play Santa.
[ Gasps ]

03:59.840 --> 04:01.206
[ Laughter ]

04:01.208 --> 04:02.908
Oh, and I can do his makeup!

04:02.910 --> 04:04.576
I interned as a makeup artist

04:04.578 --> 04:07.012
for the traveling tour
of "cats."
Ahh.

04:07.014 --> 04:08.447
Was that the summer
you were a lesbian?

04:08.449 --> 04:11.450
Good memory!
But no.

04:11.452 --> 04:12.851
No, it was the previous summer,

04:12.853 --> 04:14.453
when I met that woman
who owned the cranberry bog.

04:14.455 --> 04:15.687
Oh, right.

04:15.689 --> 04:17.022
Mm.
Right.

04:17.024 --> 04:19.258
Anyway, it'd be an honor
to play Santa.

04:19.260 --> 04:20.726
[ Laughs ]
Oh, great!

04:20.728 --> 04:22.361
It's gonna be so much fun!
Yeah.

04:24.565 --> 04:27.065
Now, this binder contains
equations that support the math

04:27.067 --> 04:29.101
of Santa's transcontinental
one-day flight.

04:29.103 --> 04:31.570
And<i> this</i> binder contains
the complete history

04:31.572 --> 04:34.273
of Santa and Evan's interactions
over the past five years.

04:34.275 --> 04:35.307
Oh.

04:35.309 --> 04:36.975
I know it's a lot,
but Evan's smart.

04:36.977 --> 04:38.810
Uh, well, he's met his match.

04:38.812 --> 04:41.647
I mean, you don't get to be one
of Orlando's top 100 dentists

04:41.649 --> 04:43.215
by not being smart.

04:43.217 --> 04:44.816
Oh, what number
in the top 100 are you?

04:44.818 --> 04:46.752
I have it all under control.
Don't worry about it.

04:46.754 --> 04:49.721
[ Laughs ]

04:49.723 --> 04:52.991
I wonder what Lorraine is up to.
[ Chuckles ]

04:52.993 --> 04:55.794
Isn't it funny how people just
come into your life, and...

04:55.796 --> 04:58.063
Yeah.
Then go?

05:01.502 --> 05:03.068
Eddie:
What's this noise?

05:03.070 --> 05:04.469
My Christmas present for mom.

05:04.471 --> 05:06.638
It's an exact replica
of the "white horse bakery"

05:06.640 --> 05:08.707
that's missing
from Jessica town.

05:10.477 --> 05:12.411
What are you gonna get mom
for Christmas?

05:12.413 --> 05:13.745
I don't know.

05:13.747 --> 05:15.414
Well, when are you
gonna figure it out?

05:15.416 --> 05:16.848
I don't know.

05:16.850 --> 05:19.151
Thoughtful presents
are always appreciated.

05:19.153 --> 05:21.787
Remember last year when I wrote
that historical novel

05:21.789 --> 05:23.822
based on grandma's life,
"a Pearl for God"?

05:23.824 --> 05:25.123
She loved it.

05:25.125 --> 05:26.525
Did she, though?

05:26.527 --> 05:27.426
Grandma!

05:27.428 --> 05:28.527
Grandma Huang: What?

05:28.529 --> 05:30.729
You got to come here!

05:33.500 --> 05:36.401
What did Emery get you last year
for Christmas?

05:37.838 --> 05:39.705
The historical novel.

05:39.707 --> 05:41.406
[ Speaking Chinese ]

05:47.948 --> 05:49.281
What?

05:49.283 --> 05:50.882
And what did<i> I</i> get you?

05:52.786 --> 05:54.019
[ Speaking Chinese ]

05:59.493 --> 06:02.227
¶¶

06:06.033 --> 06:08.166
We wish you a merry breakfast!

06:08.168 --> 06:10.068
Eat up and come meet Santa!
[ Chuckles ]

06:10.070 --> 06:12.070
Oh,
try our peppermint cornbread!

06:12.072 --> 06:14.639
Sounds gross, but tastes...

06:14.641 --> 06:15.941
Freshens your breath!

06:18.145 --> 06:20.545
I can't wait to talk to Santa
about science and math!

06:20.547 --> 06:22.981
Great, but don't ask Santa
too many questions.

06:22.983 --> 06:24.516
He's a busy man.

06:24.518 --> 06:26.918
He has enough time
to spend two hours every night

06:26.920 --> 06:29.221
talking to his mother over tea.

06:29.223 --> 06:31.223
She will always be
his favorite woman.

06:34.194 --> 06:35.660
Eddie: What happened
to your hands?

06:35.662 --> 06:38.730
I burnt my fingers using the
hot-glue gun on mom's present.

06:38.732 --> 06:41.032
We have a hot-glue gun?

06:41.034 --> 06:43.268
Why haven't we glued Evan
to the wall yet?

06:44.671 --> 06:46.037
Okay, guys!

06:46.039 --> 06:48.740
I just got word
that Santa has arrived!

06:48.742 --> 06:50.108
[ Squeals ]

06:50.110 --> 06:52.077
Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho!

06:52.079 --> 06:53.845
Merry Christmas!

06:53.847 --> 06:55.247
Santa!

06:55.249 --> 06:56.948
Come,
we have so much to discuss!

06:56.950 --> 06:58.150
[ Laughs ]

07:01.021 --> 07:03.789
¶¶

07:03.791 --> 07:05.290
So, to calculate lift,

07:05.292 --> 07:07.893
it's coefficient times density
times the velocity squared

07:07.895 --> 07:10.195
times the area of the wing
divided by two.

07:10.197 --> 07:12.697
And that's factoring in
Rudolph's body weight?

07:12.699 --> 07:14.232
Absolutely.

07:14.234 --> 07:16.268
We wouldn't want to fly too low

07:16.270 --> 07:17.969
and clip off the chimney tops.

07:17.971 --> 07:20.272
[ Chuckles ]
Heaven forbid!

07:20.274 --> 07:21.274
[ Laughs ]

07:21.275 --> 07:23.308
Marvin really looks like Santa.

07:23.310 --> 07:25.377
Is that a prosthetic nose?

07:25.379 --> 07:27.979
Yep. It's the same one
I used on skimbleshanks.

07:27.981 --> 07:30.215
That means nothing to me.

07:30.217 --> 07:34.152
[ Gasps ] Anyway, I know
it's not Christmas yet, but...

07:34.154 --> 07:37.589
I found you the perfect gift,
and I couldn't wait.

07:37.591 --> 07:39.758
[ Gasps ] Oh!

07:39.760 --> 07:41.092
The bakery?!

07:41.094 --> 07:42.994
What the Mary?
[ Laughs ]

07:42.996 --> 07:44.162
How did you get this?!

07:44.164 --> 07:45.630
Oh, Marvin's first wife

07:45.632 --> 07:47.499
left a box of Christmas
decorations in the garage,

07:47.501 --> 07:49.067
and this was in there.

07:49.069 --> 07:51.002
And some cocaine.

07:51.004 --> 07:52.904
Like I said, there were some
problems before I came along.

07:52.906 --> 07:54.573
I love it!
Yay!

07:54.575 --> 07:55.740
Oh, thank you so much!
[ Giggles ]

07:55.742 --> 07:56.808
You're welcome.

07:56.810 --> 07:57.909
Santa was great!

07:57.911 --> 07:59.277
He's so smart, and...

07:59.279 --> 08:01.780
Ho, ho, ho!

08:01.782 --> 08:03.348
Ho, ho...

08:03.350 --> 08:05.016
No!

08:05.018 --> 08:06.518
Who the hell is that?

08:06.520 --> 08:08.353
<i>I'm</i> Santa!

08:08.355 --> 08:13.892
Wait. If this Santa's Mitch,
then who's that Santa?

08:20.934 --> 08:23.268
[ Christmas music plays ]

08:26.473 --> 08:29.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:32.012 --> 08:33.879
What's going on?

08:35.015 --> 08:36.715
[ Sighs ]

08:36.717 --> 08:39.284
You know what, Evan?
It's time you know the truth.

08:39.286 --> 08:40.118
Jessica...

08:40.120 --> 08:42.287
He's figured it out, Louis.

08:42.289 --> 08:44.356
We have no choice
but to come clean.

08:45.459 --> 08:47.425
Evan, we've been lying to you.

08:49.062 --> 08:50.495
This Santa is Mitch.

08:50.497 --> 08:52.497
And look.

08:52.499 --> 08:54.132
This Santa is Marvin.
[ Chuckles ]

08:55.302 --> 08:57.168
Both of these santas are fake

08:57.170 --> 09:00.071
because the real Santa...

09:00.073 --> 09:01.306
Is Chinese.

09:01.308 --> 09:02.741
What?
What?

09:02.743 --> 09:04.576
Santa's Chinese?

09:04.578 --> 09:06.144
Yes!

09:06.146 --> 09:09.548
Why do you think all the toys
he delivers say "made in China"?

09:09.550 --> 09:10.550
Right, Louis?

09:10.551 --> 09:12.918
Uh, right.
Right.

09:12.920 --> 09:14.352
[ Stammering ]

09:14.354 --> 09:16.888
How about how Santa wears
a red suit?

09:16.890 --> 09:19.391
Nothing more Chinese
than the color red.

09:19.393 --> 09:21.326
I've never seen a Chinese Santa.

09:21.328 --> 09:23.528
Oh!
O-oh, of course you haven't.

09:23.530 --> 09:26.665
Real Santa doesn't have the time
to be standing around

09:26.667 --> 09:28.600
ringing a bell
on every street corner.

09:28.602 --> 09:30.335
Then why all the white santas?

09:30.337 --> 09:33.004
Uh, well, remember
when I first opened cattleman's

09:33.006 --> 09:35.941
and hired Mitch to be the
white face of the restaurant?

09:35.943 --> 09:38.109
Chinese Santa's doing
the same thing.

09:38.111 --> 09:42.581
Ah, all those white santas are
just Chinese Santa's mitches.

09:42.583 --> 09:44.683
Oh.

09:44.685 --> 09:47.586
Never knew this.
[ Chuckles ]

09:49.089 --> 09:51.289
I can't believe
honey got mom the bakery.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.024
Christmas is days away,
and I've got nothing.

09:53.026 --> 09:54.559
Ah, yes.

09:54.561 --> 09:56.861
This is a position
I've been in many times.

09:56.863 --> 09:58.930
If I don't come up
with something for mom,

09:58.932 --> 10:00.699
it'd be weird to give dad
his present.

10:02.302 --> 10:03.969
Ooh!
Is that made of chocolate?

10:03.971 --> 10:05.303
What am I gonna do?

10:05.305 --> 10:07.072
This is what you're gonna do.

10:07.074 --> 10:08.907
I got you.

10:08.909 --> 10:09.909
You ready?

10:09.910 --> 10:11.142
You're gonna...

10:11.144 --> 10:12.310
Let it ride!

10:13.714 --> 10:15.113
What?

10:15.115 --> 10:16.815
I said...
"Let it ride!"

10:18.118 --> 10:19.417
What does that mean?

10:19.419 --> 10:20.585
You don't do anything,

10:20.587 --> 10:22.787
and then somehow
it just works itself out.

10:22.789 --> 10:24.756
The best action is inaction.

10:24.758 --> 10:26.291
It's one of Newton's laws.

10:26.293 --> 10:27.125
No, it's not.

10:27.127 --> 10:28.460
Agree to disagree.

10:28.462 --> 10:29.728
[ Sighs ]

10:29.730 --> 10:32.998
Okay, ready to go
to Evan's holiday pageant?

10:33.000 --> 10:34.633
Ooh, are those zongzi?

10:34.635 --> 10:36.434
Uh!
These are for Chinese Santa.

10:36.436 --> 10:38.403
They're filled with proteins
and mung bean

10:38.405 --> 10:40.305
because Santa is training
for a half marathon.

10:40.307 --> 10:42.273
All right.

10:42.275 --> 10:45.110
I only went along with you
at cattleman's because of Evan,

10:45.112 --> 10:46.978
but you've got to
stop fixing Santa.

10:46.980 --> 10:49.347
I'm done.
Santa's fixed.

10:49.349 --> 10:51.116
I made him the best.

10:51.118 --> 10:53.752
I've been thinking about
what you said about Santa.

10:55.355 --> 10:56.921
It totally makes sense!

10:58.191 --> 11:00.258
Smart enough to understand
the science of flight,

11:00.260 --> 11:02.360
yet small enough
to fit down a chimney?

11:02.362 --> 11:03.862
That dude Chinese.

11:07.034 --> 11:09.100
¶¶

11:09.102 --> 11:10.368
Boom.

11:10.370 --> 11:12.037
What's this?

11:12.039 --> 11:14.806
It's a poem I wrote for mom that
we can say is from both of us.

11:14.808 --> 11:18.209
"Dear mama,
place no one above ya."

11:18.211 --> 11:21.212
Sweet lady, you are appreciated.

11:21.214 --> 11:23.048
"Don't ya know
we love ya?"

11:23.050 --> 11:24.382
This is pretty good.

11:24.384 --> 11:25.550
I know.

11:25.552 --> 11:27.619
But some of this
doesn't make sense.

11:27.621 --> 11:31.690
Like, why'd you say,
"even as a crack fiend, mama,

11:31.692 --> 11:33.558
you always was
a black queen, mama"?

11:33.560 --> 11:35.894
It's poetry, man.
Don't be so literal.

11:35.896 --> 11:37.996
I do have a logical brain.

11:37.998 --> 11:40.165
That's why I could never enjoy
nursery rhymes,

11:40.167 --> 11:41.866
like three pigs live in a house,

11:41.868 --> 11:45.003
an old woman lives in a shoe,
bears eat porridge...

11:45.005 --> 11:46.671
It's silly is what it is!

11:46.673 --> 11:49.541
I like this intensity, Emery.

11:49.543 --> 11:52.177
We should channel this
into something more positive.

11:52.179 --> 11:55.647
¶¶

11:55.649 --> 11:57.515
That's awesome!
Mom's gonna love it.

11:57.517 --> 11:59.851
Hey, I'm gonna go get a soda.

11:59.853 --> 12:01.486
You're not coming back, are you?

12:01.488 --> 12:03.154
Nope.

12:05.492 --> 12:06.691
[ Applause ]

12:06.693 --> 12:09.527
Welcome, 3rd-grade students
and parents.

12:09.529 --> 12:11.429
As you know, every year,

12:11.431 --> 12:13.998
our faculty likes to put on
a holiday show

12:14.000 --> 12:16.901
as a thank-you for
your hard work and dedication.

12:16.903 --> 12:19.037
[ Applause ]
Whoo!

12:19.039 --> 12:23.174
In our past shows, we've had
visits from Santa, Rudolph,

12:23.176 --> 12:26.111
and little-people elves,
who, with gusto,

12:26.113 --> 12:28.513
threw themselves into the crowd
to be passed around.

12:32.285 --> 12:35.353
However, a new state law
was just passed

12:35.355 --> 12:37.288
called "Kathy's rule,"

12:37.290 --> 12:40.558
which prohibits
any religious, spiritual,

12:40.560 --> 12:45.196
or gender-y connotations in
state-funded children's theater.

12:45.198 --> 12:50.769
So this year, please welcome the
pan-cultural seasonal entity.

12:53.106 --> 12:55.340
I respect you!

12:57.077 --> 12:59.144
[ Audience murmuring ]

12:59.146 --> 13:00.812
Where's Santa?

13:00.814 --> 13:03.047
Firmly rooted
in Christian tradition,

13:03.049 --> 13:05.550
unlike panny here,
who is all things

13:05.552 --> 13:08.486
because it is nothing.

13:08.488 --> 13:12.090
But it's Christmas.
There should be Santa.

13:12.092 --> 13:13.625
[ Audience murmurs
in agreement ]

13:13.627 --> 13:15.126
Santa's the best.

13:15.128 --> 13:18.129
[ Applause ]

13:18.131 --> 13:20.498
He's kind and generous
and caring.

13:20.500 --> 13:22.467
He sure is.
That's right.

13:23.670 --> 13:25.703
And he's Chinese!

13:28.241 --> 13:29.641
[ Audience murmuring ]

13:32.946 --> 13:36.181
Who wants to see panny dance?

13:43.156 --> 13:44.622
¶¶

13:44.624 --> 13:46.457
[ indistinct shouting ]

13:46.459 --> 13:48.126
Santa is not Chinese!

13:48.128 --> 13:49.861
Yes, he is!

13:49.863 --> 13:51.196
That doesn't even make sense!

13:51.198 --> 13:53.097
Okay, everybody calm down!

13:53.099 --> 13:54.699
Stop yelling at children!

13:54.701 --> 13:57.135
And why can't Santa be Chinese?

13:57.137 --> 13:59.771
Everybody's on board with a
fat man flying around the world,

13:59.773 --> 14:01.706
just so long as he's white?

14:01.708 --> 14:04.776
Santa's not fat!
He's big-boned!

14:04.778 --> 14:07.879
[ Shouting continues ]

14:07.881 --> 14:09.848
¶¶

14:09.850 --> 14:12.817
¶ don't ya know we love ya,
sweet lady? ¶

14:12.819 --> 14:15.453
¶ dear mama ¶

14:15.455 --> 14:18.223
¶ place no one above ya,
sweet lady ¶

14:18.225 --> 14:21.492
¶ you are appreciated ¶

14:21.494 --> 14:24.028
¶<i> ...all the sweet things</i>
<i>you did for me</i> ¶

14:24.030 --> 14:26.898
¶<i> and even though I act crazy</i> ¶

14:26.900 --> 14:29.801
¶<i> I gotta thank the lord</i>
<i>that you made me</i> ¶

14:29.803 --> 14:32.403
Eddie!
¶<i> there are no words</i>
<i>that can express how I feel</i> ¶

14:32.405 --> 14:33.705
¶<i> you never kept a secret</i> ¶

14:33.707 --> 14:35.640
¶<i> always stayed real</i> ¶

14:35.642 --> 14:37.675
¶<i> and I appreciate</i>
<i>how you raised me</i> ¶

14:37.677 --> 14:39.644
Eddie, you didn't write a poem.

14:39.646 --> 14:41.379
You plagiarized a rap song.

14:41.381 --> 14:43.414
I didn't plagiarize.

14:43.416 --> 14:45.016
I sampled.

14:45.018 --> 14:47.886
We can't give mom 2pac lyrics
as her present.

14:47.888 --> 14:49.420
Christmas is two days away.

14:49.422 --> 14:50.422
What are we gonna do?

14:52.158 --> 14:53.024
Don't say it.

14:53.026 --> 14:55.059
Let it ride!

14:55.061 --> 14:56.061
No kick?

14:56.930 --> 14:58.696
I'm wearing umbros.

14:58.698 --> 15:00.164
Don't want you to get an eyeful.

15:00.166 --> 15:01.432
You feel me.

15:03.703 --> 15:06.738
Well, that got out of hand fast.

15:06.740 --> 15:08.439
I can't believe they chased
that gray blob

15:08.441 --> 15:09.574
through the parking lot.

15:09.576 --> 15:11.509
You guys know me!
I'm Paul Andrews!

15:11.511 --> 15:12.677
Chrissy's father!

15:12.679 --> 15:14.145
Cut him off!

15:16.616 --> 15:18.549
Evan, are you okay?

15:18.551 --> 15:19.684
I'm just confused.

15:19.686 --> 15:21.352
You said Santa's not white,

15:21.354 --> 15:23.855
and everyone at school says
he's not Chinese.

15:23.857 --> 15:25.323
I don't know what to believe.

15:28.895 --> 15:30.895
I-I didn't mean
for this to happen.

15:30.897 --> 15:34.866
I just... I just wanted
to make Santa the best for him.

15:34.868 --> 15:36.067
I know you did.

15:36.069 --> 15:39.604
I need to find a way
to make this right.

15:41.775 --> 15:44.475
Honey, I need your help.

15:47.747 --> 15:48.880
[ Creaking ]

16:00.060 --> 16:01.659
[ Rustling ]

16:03.663 --> 16:05.530
Santa?

16:08.668 --> 16:10.902
Santa<i> is</i> Chinese!

16:10.904 --> 16:12.737
Yes.

16:15.775 --> 16:17.742
But you're a woman.

16:17.744 --> 16:19.944
Yes.

16:19.946 --> 16:21.312
Then why do you have a beard?

16:21.314 --> 16:23.815
This is mole hair.

16:23.817 --> 16:29.620
It all grows out
of two very lucky moles.

16:29.622 --> 16:31.756
I've never heard
of a woman Santa.

16:31.758 --> 16:34.993
You think a man
is thoughtful enough

16:34.995 --> 16:38.963
to give presents to everyone
in the world?

16:38.965 --> 16:42.867
Do you think a man
is organized enough

16:42.869 --> 16:47.705
to make a list of the behavior
of every single boy and girl?

16:47.707 --> 16:52.477
You know those street signs
that say "men at work"?

16:52.479 --> 16:57.115
Women don't need those
because it is understood.

16:57.117 --> 16:59.517
But all the santas
I ever see are white men.

16:59.519 --> 17:02.053
They all work for me.

17:02.055 --> 17:05.390
I am the wholesaler.

17:05.392 --> 17:08.526
They are my middlemen.

17:08.528 --> 17:11.162
But why are you here tonight?

17:11.164 --> 17:12.563
It's not Christmas Eve yet.

17:12.565 --> 17:16.567
I come on December 23rd...

17:16.569 --> 17:18.536
And I hide the presents.

17:18.538 --> 17:22.006
Then my white santas come
Christmas Eve

17:22.008 --> 17:25.009
and put the presents
out under the tree.

17:25.011 --> 17:29.480
I allow them to take credit,
but I am the boss.

17:29.482 --> 17:32.216
This is why I am called...

17:32.218 --> 17:35.420
Lao ban Santa.

17:35.422 --> 17:37.255
Boss Santa!

17:37.257 --> 17:38.257
That's right.

17:38.258 --> 17:39.991
I'd better go.

17:39.993 --> 17:43.394
My lebaron is idling
in the driveway.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.363
You drive a lebaron?

17:45.365 --> 17:46.531
It's a lease.

17:46.533 --> 17:48.499
Better for tax purposes.

17:51.037 --> 17:55.440
You must promise
never to tell anyone about me,

17:55.442 --> 17:58.676
not even your brothers.

17:58.678 --> 18:01.045
You are a special soul...

18:01.047 --> 18:06.217
One who believes in magic
but still has a scientific mind.

18:06.219 --> 18:07.952
Like me.

18:07.954 --> 18:10.388
So you<i> are</i> a scientist!

18:10.390 --> 18:11.856
Well, of course!

18:11.858 --> 18:16.094
I have a j.D., m.D.,
dds, phd,

18:16.096 --> 18:18.563
and I am a notary.

18:18.565 --> 18:21.799
Remember...
Always be the best.

18:21.801 --> 18:26.104
Study hard
and eat more vegetables.

18:26.106 --> 18:29.073
My fat friend j.J. Says candy
is America's vegetable.

18:29.075 --> 18:32.577
Maybe less time with j.J.

18:32.579 --> 18:34.479
Merry Christmas, Evan.

18:34.481 --> 18:36.647
Merry Christmas, Lao ban Santa.

19:08.348 --> 19:09.747
[ Floorboard creaks ]

19:09.749 --> 19:11.749
Evan?
Everything okay?

19:11.751 --> 19:13.584
[ Chuckles ]

19:13.586 --> 19:15.419
Everything's great.

19:18.191 --> 19:19.357
[ Door closes ]

19:21.194 --> 19:22.426
Uh. Aah! Aah!
[ Muffled scream ]

19:22.428 --> 19:24.395
Shh.
I have a lot to tell you.

19:28.201 --> 19:31.102
"Guarding Tess."
Thank you, Eddie.

19:32.705 --> 19:34.105
Why you so nervous, man?

19:34.107 --> 19:36.507
Because it's Christmas morning,

19:36.509 --> 19:39.610
and all I have for mom are
these film-canister earrings.

19:39.612 --> 19:41.212
This is not who I am.

19:41.214 --> 19:42.280
[ Boomerang whooshes,
glass breaks ]

19:42.282 --> 19:43.381
Ooh!

19:45.451 --> 19:47.018
Oh, no!

19:47.020 --> 19:48.819
It's the bakery!

19:48.821 --> 19:50.855
Mrs. smithyman the shopkeeper

19:50.857 --> 19:54.158
was just getting over
her husband's suicide.

19:54.160 --> 19:55.126
Dark.

19:55.128 --> 19:57.628
Don't worry, mom.
We got you.

19:59.332 --> 20:01.499
Emery made it.

20:01.501 --> 20:03.134
This is amazing.

20:03.136 --> 20:04.835
You made this by yourself?

20:04.837 --> 20:06.537
Yeah, it's perfect to scale.

20:06.539 --> 20:10.141
Thank you.
I love it.

20:10.143 --> 20:11.576
And I made you these earrings.

20:11.578 --> 20:13.377
Thank you, Eddie.

20:13.379 --> 20:16.280
I'll put them with the paperclip
anklet you gave me last year.

20:19.185 --> 20:21.686
Maybe there is something
to thoughtful presents.

20:21.688 --> 20:24.555
I was gonna say maybe there's
something to letting it ride.

20:24.557 --> 20:26.157
You ready?

20:26.159 --> 20:28.659
One, two, three.

20:28.661 --> 20:30.261
Let it ride!
Ha!

20:32.098 --> 20:34.632
It's like
I'm kicking into a mirror.

20:35.735 --> 20:37.702
Wow, Evan,
look how many presents

20:37.704 --> 20:39.670
Santa left you last night.

20:39.672 --> 20:41.105
Yes.

20:41.107 --> 20:43.841
So many presents
from<i> regular</i> Santa,

20:43.843 --> 20:46.510
which he brought in <i>last</i> night.

20:46.512 --> 20:49.413
